FBIS4-43424 "drweu116_h_94002" FBIS-WEU-94-116 Daily Report 16 Jun 1994 GERMANY Berlusconi Begins Official Visit 16 Jun Berlusconi Begins Official Visit 16 Jun Rejects Racism LD1606111494 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1046 GMT 16 Jun 94 LD1606111494 Berlin DDP/ADN German BFN [Excerpt] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- Silvio Berlusconi, Italy's new prime minister, has pledged that his government will respect the principles of liberty and tolerance. All types of racism and antisemitism must be consigned to the past, Berlusconi said in Bonn today at the start of his visit to Germany. He also pointed out that Italy and Germany currently face similar problems in areas such as unemployment, where a joint approach is needed. [passage omitted]
